={
  "model": "llama3.3:70b",
  "prompt": "You are a B2B sales intelligence analyst for Leadership by Design (LBD), a South African leadership development company.

Analyse this prospect and return a JSON object with scoring:

Company: {{ $json.company_name }}
Industry: {{ $json.industry_vertical }}
Employee Count: {{ $json.employee_count }}
Decision Maker: {{ $json.decision_maker_name }} ({{ $json.decision_maker_title }})
Pain Signals: {{ $json.pain_signals }}
Growth Signals: {{ $json.growth_signals }}
OS-Readiness Score: {{ $json.os_readiness_score }}
Engagement Hook: {{ $json.engagement_hook }}
Recommended Programme: {{ $json.recommended_programme }}

Return ONLY this JSON (no markdown, no explanation):
{
  "buying_likelihood": <1-10>,
  "engagement_fit": <1-10>,
  "budget_indicator": "high/medium/low",
  "decision_timeline": "immediate/quarter/half-year/unknown",
  "recommended_approach": "<one sentence: direct pitch / diagnostic offer / content nurture / event invite>",
  "key_objection": "<most likely objection>",
  "estimated_deal_value": <number in ZAR>
}",
  "stream": false,
  "options": {
    "temperature": 0.3
  }
}

={
  "model": "llama3.3:70b",
  "prompt": "You are Kevin, founder of Leadership by Design. You write ultra-casual, lowercase emails. 3 sentences max. You use OS-language framing (operating system for leadership). You never sound corporate or salesy.

Context about the prospect:
- Company: {{ $json.company_name }}
- Decision Maker: {{ $json.decision_maker_name }} ({{ $json.decision_maker_title }})
- Pain Signal: {{ $json.engagement_hook }}
- Recommended Programme: {{ $json.recommended_programme }}
- Industry: {{ $json.industry_vertical }}

Kevin's voice rules:
1. Always lowercase (except proper nouns)
2. Ultra-casual, like texting a friend
3. Max 3 sentences
4. Reference their specific pain signal
5. Use OS metaphor naturally (don't force it)
6. End with a soft CTA (diagnostic, not a meeting)
7. Subject line: lowercase, intriguing, under 6 words

Kevin's signature:
kevin
leadership by design
built by design. not by default.

Return ONLY this JSON (no markdown):
{
  "subject": "<subject line>",
  "body": "<full email body including signature>",
  "cta_type": "diagnostic/content/event/direct"
}",
  "stream": false,
  "options": {
    "temperature": 0.7
  }
}

={
  "model": "claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
  "max_tokens": 1024,
  "system": "You are an email proofreader. Your ONLY job is to fix grammar and typos. Do NOT change the voice, tone, style, or content. Keep everything lowercase as-is. Keep it ultra-casual. Keep the OS metaphors. Return ONLY the corrected JSON with subject and body fields. No markdown.",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Fix only grammar/typos in this email JSON. Keep the casual voice exactly as-is:\n\n{{ JSON.stringify($json.email_data || { subject: $json.subject, body: $json.body }) }}"
    }
  ]
}

={
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "text": {
        "type": "plain_text",
        "text": "🔥 HOT Prospect Found — Claude Connector"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "fields": [
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "*Company:*\n{{ $json.company_name || $node['2. Parse Prospects to Rows'].json.company_name }}"
        },
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "*Decision Maker:*\n{{ $json.decision_maker_name || $node['2. Parse Prospects to Rows'].json.decision_maker_name }} ({{ $json.decision_maker_title || $node['2. Parse Prospects to Rows'].json.decision_maker_title }})"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "fields": [
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "*OS-Readiness:*\n{{ $json.os_readiness_score || $node['2. Parse Prospects to Rows'].json.os_readiness_score }}/10"
        },
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "*Programme:*\n{{ $json.recommended_programme || $node['2. Parse Prospects to Rows'].json.recommended_programme }}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "text": {
        "type": "mrkdwn",
        "text": "*Pain Signal:*\n{{ $json.engagement_hook || $node['2. Parse Prospects to Rows'].json.engagement_hook }}"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "divider"
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "text": {
        "type": "mrkdwn",
        "text": "*Email Draft:*\n```Subject: {{ $json.subject || '' }}\n\n{{ $json.body || '' }}```"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "actions",
      "elements": [
        {
          "type": "button",
          "text": {
            "type": "plain_text",
            "text": "✅ Send Email"
          },
          "style": "primary",
          "value": "send_{{ $json.decision_maker_email_guess || $node['2. Parse Prospects to Rows'].json.decision_maker_email_guess }}"
        },
        {
          "type": "button",
          "text": {
            "type": "plain_text",
            "text": "✏️ Edit First"
          },
          "value": "edit_{{ $json.id || '' }}"
        },
        {
          "type": "button",
          "text": {
            "type": "plain_text",
            "text": "❌ Skip"
          },
          "style": "danger",
          "value": "skip_{{ $json.id || '' }}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

={
  "raw": "{{ Buffer.from(
    'To: ' + ($json.decision_maker_email_guess || $node['2. Parse Prospects to Rows'].json.decision_maker_email_guess) + '\r\n' +
    'Subject: ' + ($json.subject || '') + '\r\n' +
    'Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8\r\n' +
    '\r\n' +
    ($json.body || '')
  ).toString('base64url') }}"
}
